Pre-Game Insights: The match is expected to be a cagey affair as neither team wants to risk having a key player suffer an injury.
The Socceroos are expected to have the edge due to their strong continuity and solid form versus Asian opposition.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match will be played at Baniyas Stadium in the United Arab Emirates (UAE).
Bahrain have never beaten the Socceroos in their five previous meetings, suffering a 1-0 defeat the last time around at the 2011 Asian Cup.
Others: Bahrain's manager Juan Antonio Pizzi has begun his tenure well, suffering just one defeat since taking charge.
Australia's team includes four players who will be seeking their first caps with the Socceroos: John Iredale, Patrick Yazbek, Gethin Jones, and Kusini Yengi.
